cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with modifying learning to produce representations that are minimally synergistic. It also involves exploring different ways of quantifying synergy, which is a key aspect of machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with disentangling the true factors of variation underlying data, which is a common goal in AI research. 

The paper also involves working with images, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Additionally, the paper deals with neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
